flow-state|05_Context|Flow State|Flow State describes the conditions under which attention becomes absorbed, effort feels steady, and progress starts to feel self-sustaining.|This domain looks at the conditions that make useful work easier to enter and easier to keep going across focus, ideas, movement, and conversation.|Read the ranked signals as likely flow conditions, not as a fixed identity. Lower-ranked signals are range to use deliberately, not weaknesses.|This is a ranked reading of the conditions most likely to help flow start, deepen, reset, and become useful.|active|flow-state::intro
06_Orientation
domain_key|pattern_key|score_shape|rank_1_signal_key|rank_2_signal_key|rank_3_signal_key|rank_4_signal_key|orientation_title|orientation_summary|score_shape_summary|rank_1_phrase|rank_2_phrase|rank_3_phrase|rank_4_phrase|status|lookup_key
flow-state|physical_rhythm_deep_focus_creative_movement_social_exchange|concentrated|physical_rhythm|deep_focus|creative_movement|social_exchange|Physical rhythm first|Start by looking at Physical rhythm. Bring in a way to pause, concentrate, and make the work more substantial when the work needs more range.|One signal is doing most of the work here. Physical rhythm is the clearest starting point for this result.|Your main route is movement, pace, and a change of physical state.|What gives it depth: focused time with one demanding problem.|What adds energy: ideas, expression, and new angles.|What to use deliberately: conversation and feedback before the work becomes too private.|draft|flow-state::physical_rhythm_deep_focus_creative_movement_social_exchange::concentrated
07_Recognition
domain_key|pattern_key|score_shape|rank_1_signal_key|rank_2_signal_key|rank_3_signal_key|rank_4_signal_key|headline|recognition_statement|recognition_expansion|status|lookup_key
flow-state|physical_rhythm_deep_focus_creative_movement_social_exchange|concentrated|physical_rhythm|deep_focus|creative_movement|social_exchange|Flow starts when your body gets involved|You are most likely to find flow when movement, pace, or physical engagement helps attention switch on.|This pattern often shows up when sitting still makes the work feel harder than it needs to. You may think better while walking, pacing, making, training, sorting, practising, or working with a steady rhythm. Deep Focus then helps you stay with what matters once your energy is engaged. Creative Movement can bring in new angles when action starts to become repetitive. Social Exchange becomes useful when the work needs to make sense to someone else.|active|flow-state::physical_rhythm_deep_focus_creative_movement_social_exchange::concentrated
08_Signal_Roles
domain_key|signal_key|signal_label|rank_position|rank_role|title|description|productive_expression|risk_pattern|development_note|status|lookup_key
flow-state|physical_rhythm|Physical Rhythm|1|dominant|Physical Rhythm as the starting point|Physical Rhythm is where this pattern usually begins. Flow is most likely when movement, pace, physical work, or a clear rhythm gives attention something to organise around.|This can help you access energy, focus, and progress when thinking harder would not work as well.|The risk is staying in motion after the work now needs stillness, feedback, or a clear decision.|Use movement to enter the work, then pause long enough to choose what matters next.|active|flow-state::physical_rhythm::1
flow-state|deep_focus|Deep Focus|2|secondary|Deep Focus as the source of substance|Deep Focus helps this pattern become more than useful motion. It lets you stay with the important part once the body has helped attention switch on.|This can turn active engagement into careful work with depth, judgement, and follow-through.|The risk is moving on before the focused part of the work has had enough time.|Use focus after movement has opened the door, especially when the next step needs care.|active|flow-state::deep_focus::2
flow-state|creative_movement|Creative Movement|3|tertiary|Creative Movement as a way to vary the route|Creative Movement helps when rhythm starts to become too repetitive. It brings new angles, alternatives, and a different way to approach the work.|This can keep practical action from becoming automatic or too narrow.|The risk is adding new options when the useful move is to finish, choose, or simplify.|Use ideas to refresh the route, not to avoid the next clear decision.|active|flow-state::creative_movement::3
flow-state|social_exchange|Social Exchange|4|least_expressed|Social Exchange as useful outside testing|Social Exchange may not be your first way into flow, but it can help when the work needs to be checked beyond your own experience of doing it.|This can help you find out whether the result is clear, useful, and understandable to another person.|The risk is relying on your own sense of momentum after the work needs an outside response.|Invite one useful person to test the result before you keep moving it forward.|active|flow-state::social_exchange::4
09_Pattern_Mechanics
domain_key|pattern_key|score_shape|rank_1_signal_key|rank_2_signal_key|rank_3_signal_key|rank_4_signal_key|mechanics_title|core_mechanism|why_it_shows_up|what_it_protects|status|lookup_key
flow-state|physical_rhythm_deep_focus_creative_movement_social_exchange|concentrated|physical_rhythm|deep_focus|creative_movement|social_exchange|Why movement helps attention switch on|This pattern works by using movement, rhythm, or physical engagement to make attention easier to access. Once the body is involved, Deep Focus helps the work gain substance, Creative Movement adds variation, and Social Exchange checks whether the result lands outside your own process.|It may show up because action gives the mind a practical place to start. The work can feel easier to enter when pace, movement, or a repeated rhythm gives attention something to follow.|It protects energy, progress, and the ability to begin when stillness would make the work feel stuck. The trade-off is that motion can continue after the work needs a pause.|active|flow-state::physical_rhythm_deep_focus_creative_movement_social_exchange::concentrated
10_Pattern_Synthesis
domain_key|pattern_key|score_shape|rank_1_signal_key|rank_2_signal_key|rank_3_signal_key|rank_4_signal_key|synthesis_title|gift|trap|takeaway|synthesis_text|status|lookup_key
flow-state|physical_rhythm_deep_focus_creative_movement_social_exchange|concentrated|physical_rhythm|deep_focus|creative_movement|social_exchange|Movement that becomes focused progress|You can use movement and rhythm to access attention when sitting still would not work as well.|You may stay in action after the work now needs stillness, feedback, or a clear choice.|Let movement open the work, then pause to focus and choose.|This pattern is strongest when physical engagement gives attention a way in. Deep Focus helps you stay with the part that matters. Creative Movement keeps the work from becoming only repetitive action. Social Exchange adds the outside test that shows whether the result makes sense beyond your own momentum.|active|flow-state::physical_rhythm_deep_focus_creative_movement_social_exchange::concentrated
